library(tidyverse)
library(gmodels)
library(lme4)
library(lmerTest)

library(MASS)

##### set up some cool functions ####
variable_names <- list(
  "WT" = expression(bolditalic("Zic2")^bolditalic("+/+")),
  "HET" = expression(bolditalic("Zic2")^bolditalic("Ku/+"))
)

group_names <- list(
  "HET Ethanol" = expression(bolditalic("Zic2")^bolditalic("Ku/+")|"Ethanol" ),
  "HET Normal" = expression(bolditalic("Zic2")^bolditalic("Ku/+")|"Vehicle" ),
  "WT Ethanol" = expression(bolditalic("Zic2")^bolditalic("+/+")|"Ethanol"),
  "WT Normal" = expression(bolditalic("Zic2")^bolditalic("+/+")|"Vehicle") )

variable_labeller <- function(variable,value){return(variable_names[value])}

group_labeller <- function(variable,value){return(group_names[value])}

#####################################
#PALLIUM
####################################
###### read and set up data ######
pal <- read_csv("/media/sf_vmshare/Forebrain_R/MicroCT_HGJ_2020_Kyle_final_volume_Analysis_pal_lum.csv", 
                 col_types = cols(fb_cube_normalised = col_number(), 
                                  lum_cube_norm = col_number(), lum_norm_ew = col_number()))
## Warning: Missing column names filled in: 'X12' [12], 'X13' [13],
## 'X20' [20], 'X21' [21]
## Warning: The following named parsers don't match the column names:
## fb_cube_normalised, lum_cube_norm, lum_norm_ew
pal <- pal %>% mutate(Group = paste(Genotype,Water.supply), fb_norm_otsu = (lum_seg/otsu_wev))  %>% rename(WEV = otsu_wev) 


pal$Dam<-factor(pal$Dam)
pal$Water.supply<-factor(pal$Water.supply, levels=c("Normal","Ethanol"))

pal <- arrange(transform(pal, Genotype=factor(Genotype,levels=c("WT","HET"))) )


##Summary of Data###
Summarize(pal_norm_otsu~Genotype+Water.supply,
          data=pal,
          digits=4)

  facet_wrap(~Group, labeller = group_labeller)+
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 0))+

###########Statistics###############

#Very important ANOVA
pal_anova<-lm(pal_norm_otsu~Genotype+Water.supply+Water.supply*Genotype+WEV, data = pal)

#Diagnostic plots for that ANOVA - all assumptions are met. The standardised residuals on the Q-Q plot are off at the 
#end but this doesn't effect the ANOVA as these point don't greatly affect the mean. 

plot(pal_anova)

#Statistical test to test if residuals are normally distributed - they are which is good

shapiro.test(resid(pal_anova))
## 
##  Shapiro-Wilk normality test
## 
## data:  resid(pal_anova)
## W = 0.96616, p-value = 0.00525
#Two-way ANOVA

anova(pal_anova)

#Very important ANOVAs
tlv_anova<-lm(lum_norm_otsu~Genotype+Water.supply+Water.supply*Genotype+WEV, data = tlv)

#Diagnostic plots for that ANOVA - all assumptions are met. The standardised residuals on the Q-Q plot are off at the 
#end but this doesn't effect the ANOVA as these point don't greatly affect the mean. 
plot(tlv_anova)

#Statistical test to test if residuals are normally distributed - they are which is good
shapiro.test(resid(tlv_anova))
## 
##  Shapiro-Wilk normality test
## 
## data:  resid(tlv_anova)
## W = 0.98176, p-value = 0.1129
#Two-way ANOVA
anova(tlv_anova)
